issue.title: __dirname is not defined when trying to create assessment

labels.name: type: question
labels.description: Request for information or clarification. Not an issue.

issue.body:
#### Environment details

  - which product (packages/*): @google-cloud/recaptcha-enterprise 4.1.0
  - OS: macOS
  - Node.js version: 20.9.0
  - npm version: 10.0.0
  - google-cloud-node version: ?

#### Steps to reproduce

Create Node.js ESM application.
Create assessment as instructed in documentation.
Build the app with ESBuild (probably irrelevant, because related directly to __dirname not defined in ESM environment, but mentioning it for completeness)

This causes the following error:

```
Exception: __dirname is not defined
Stack: ReferenceError: __dirname is not defined
    at ../node_modules/google-gax/build/src/grpc.js (/dist/submit/index.js:60459:41)
    at __require2 (/dist/submit/index.js:17:51)
    at ../node_modules/google-gax/build/src/index.js (/dist/submit/index.js:80590:18)
    at __require2 (/dist/submit/index.js:17:51)
    at new RecaptchaEnterpriseServiceClient2 (/dist/submit/index.js:80793:25)
    at createAssessment (/dist/submit/index.js:112803:22)
```

comment.body:
What I mean is that it seems __dirname is the only thing breaking ESM compatibility, so just replacing this bit with something else would make it far easier for ESM folks :)

BTW, ESM as default is now an experimental flag in Node.js 21, so I expect somewhere around Node.js 24 far more people will be hitting this.

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>josdejong/mathjs (mathjs)</summary>

### [`v12.0.0`](https://togithub.com/josdejong/mathjs/blob/HEAD/HISTORY.md#2023-10-26-1200)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/josdejong/mathjs/compare/v11.12.0...v12.0.0)

Breaking changes:

-   Fix [#​2879](https://togithub.com/josdejong/mathjs/issues/2879), [#​2927](https://togithub.com/josdejong/mathjs/issues/2927), [#​3014](https://togithub.com/josdejong/mathjs/issues/3014): change the confusing interface of `eigs` ([#​3037](https://togithub.com/josdejong/mathjs/issues/3037)),
    thanks [@​gwhitney](https://togithub.com/gwhitney).
    Before, functions `eigs` returned an object:
        { values: MathCollection; vectors: MathCollection }
    where `vectors` was a 2d matrix of which the columns contained the vectors.
    This is changed to `eigs` returning an object:
        { 
          values: MathCollection
          eigenvectors: Array<{
            value: number | BigNumber
            vector: MathCollection
          }>
        }
    Where `eigenvectors` is an array containing an object with the corresponding
    eigenvalue and vector.
-   Refactored the TypeScript type definitions to make them work with a `NodeNext`
    module resolution ([#​3079](https://togithub.com/josdejong/mathjs/issues/3079), [#​2919](https://togithub.com/josdejong/mathjs/issues/2919)).
    -   Type `MathJsStatic` is renamed to `MathJsInstance`.
    -   Type `FactoryDependencies` is deprecated, use `MathJsFactory` instead, and
        import dependency maps directly from the library.
-   Change the assignment operator of `.toTex()` output from `:=` to `=` (see
